Asset Routing Update

- All runtime image assets, including packaging images, have been moved to D:\PixelSmile\imgs.
- D:\PixelSmile\imgs\Origin is backup-only and should not be used by application logic.
- SceneForge should reference images from D:\PixelSmile\imgs during local development, but image assets should not be pushed to GitHub.

SceneForge Atmosphere Flow Update

- Before customization starts, collect customer name and contact in the persistent top bar. This is only used to match generated images to a customer.
- Product shape selection now reads local product assets from D:\PixelSmile\imgs and records the selected product before CeramicFusion.
- CeramicFusion handoff is currently a UI placeholder. Expected return path is D:\PixelSmile\imgs\<product-category>\customers\<customer-name>.
- After CeramicFusion returns a fused product draft, SceneForge should use that draft as a fixed source image for atmosphere generation instead of regenerating product shape or count.

